1. The strip() function removes any white spaces from either end of a string. Used as <string_variable>.strip()

2. lower() or upper() can be used to change case of strings. Used similar to strip().

3. replace() is used to replace one or more characters in a string. Example :
a = "Hello, World!"
print(a.replace("H", "J"))

4. The split() method splits the string into substrings if it finds instances of the separator:
a = "Hello, World!"
print(a.split(",")) # returns ['Hello', ' World!']
